Ing '''''Ocimum tenuiflorum''''' (mayayaus mu rin '''tulsi''',  '''tulasī''' (तुलसी‌) keng [[Sanskrit]],(तुलसी‌) keng [[Nepali]],  (‌তুলসী) keng [[Bangla]], (तुळस) keng [[Marathi]], (तुलसी‌) keng [[Hindi]], ''tulasi'' (తులసి) keng [[Telugu]], ('''തുളസി''') keng [[Malayalam]],  (துளசி) keng [[Tamil language|Tamil]], (ತುಳಸಿ) keng [[Kannada language|Kannada]], '''Maduruthala''' keng [[Sinhalese language|Sinhalese]]) metung yang mabanglung tanaman keng familiang [[Lamiaceae]]. Matulid ya talakad ampong masanga yang tanaman 30-60&nbsp;cm katas ampong mabulbul ya tangke ampong katamtamtaman ya sumangid a aluntiang a bulung a masikan ya bau. Deng bulung atin lang [[petiole (botany)|petiole]]s, ampong pa[[ovate]], anggang mga 5&nbsp;cm kaba, keraklan mika balamu mgalating ipan. Ding sampaga anti la mong mebugbug a kule pakaba lang [[racemes]] king malapit a (whorls).<ref>{{cite book|last=Warrier|first=P K|title=Indian Medicinal Plants|publisher=Orient Longman|year=1995|page=168}}</ref> Atin aduang pung a  [[morphotype]] a masese king India—[[aluntiang]]-bulung (Sri o kaya Lakshmi tulsi) ampong bugbug kule bulung (Krishna tulsi).<ref>{{cite journal|last=Kothari|first=S K|coauthors=Bhattacharya, A K, et al.|date=November/December 2005|title=Volatile Constituents in Oil from Different Plant Parts of Methyl Eugenol-Rich Ocimum tenuiflorum L.f. (syn. O. sanctum L.) Grown in South India|journal=Journal of Essential Oil Research: JEOR|url=http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qa4091/is_200511/ai_n15935884/pg_1|accessdate=2008-09-05}}</ref> Atin mu rin aliwa a pinduan ning ''Ocimum tenuiflorum'' a magagamit keng pamaglutu  kareng  [[Thai]], at madalerayan yang bilang '''Thai holy basil''', o '''kha phrao''' (กะเพรา)<ref>Staples, ''ibid''.</ref>—e dapat mababligo keng "Thai Basil", a pinduan ning  ''[[Ocimum basilicum]]''.


